      <h1 class='title'>Review Body on Senior Salaries: Parliamentary Pay and Allowances</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='lords-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 21 October 2004 vol 665 c33WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_33ws' title='Col. 33WS &mdash; HL Deb 21 October 2004 vol 665 c33WS' name='column_33ws' href='#column_33ws' rel='bookmark'>33WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0665P0-09519'>
        <a name='S5LV0665P0_20041021_LWS_1'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/ms-valerie-amos' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0665P0_20041021_LWS_1' title='Link to this speech by Ms Valerie Amos' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/ms-valerie-amos" title="Ms Valerie Amos">The Lord President of the Council (Baroness Amos)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S5LV0665P0-09519">The Government have laid before both Houses the Review Body on Senior Salaries report on parliamentary pay and allowances 2004. Copies are available in the Printed Paper Office and the Library of the House. I am grateful to John Baker and the members of the review body for their work. The Government have noted their recommendations on pay, allowances and pensions. Implementation of these recommendations will be a matter for decision by Parliament.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
